---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — Return App" description="Privacy Policy for the Return mobile application." lang="en">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 pt-32 pb-24">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-50 leading-tight mb-2">Privacy Policy.</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 font-light mb-10">Last Updated: June 30, 2026</p>

    <p class="text-[15px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Your privacy is paramount. <strong class="text-slate-100 font-medium">Return</strong> ("the App") is designed around the principle of <strong class="text-slate-100 font-medium">Privacy by Design</strong>. This Privacy Policy explains how we interact with data when you use the App and our website hosted via GitHub Pages (the "Service").
    </p>
    <p class="text-[15px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-10">
      We comply with the <strong class="text-slate-100 font-medium">Swiss Federal Act on Data Protection (FADP/DSG)</strong> and, where applicable, the <strong class="text-slate-100 font-medium">General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)</strong>.
    </p>

    <hr class="border-slate-800 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-50 mb-4">1. Data Controller</h2>
    <p class="text-[15px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-10">
      Since Return is operated by a private individual based in Zürich, Switzerland, you can contact the data controller directly regarding any privacy inquiries at: 
      <a href="mailto:info@returnapp.org" class="text-sapphire-400 hover:text-sapphire-300 transition-colors">info@returnapp.org</a>
    </p>

    <hr class="border-slate-800 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-50 mb-4">2. Core App Data: Local-Only Storage</h2>
    <p class="text-[15px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">
      When you use Return to log breathing sessions or track your daily mood, <strong class="text-slate-100 font-medium">this data is saved exclusively on your device's local storage.</strong>
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-[15px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-10 pl-2">
      <li><strong class="text-slate-100 font-medium">No Server Uploads:</strong> We do not collect, view, store, or transmit your breathing logs or mood data to any external servers.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-slate-100 font-medium">Your Control:</strong> Within the App, you have the built-in capability to instantly delete all your data or download your complete history in a standard .csv file.</li>
    </ul>

    <hr class="border-slate-800 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-50 mb-4">3. Data Collected by Third Parties</h2>
    <p class="text-[15px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-6">
      While we do not personally collect your data, the App utilizes standard third-party developer tools and ecosystems (Apple and Google) to function, process payments, and improve performance. These third parties collect data according to their own privacy policies:
    </p>
    
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-10 border border-slate-800 rounded-lg">
      <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse text-[14px]">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/50">
            <th class="p-4 font-medium text-slate-100 w-1/4">Provider</th>
            <th class="p-4 font-medium text-slate-100 w-1/4">Purpose</th>
            <th class="p-4 font-medium text-slate-100 w-2/4">Data Type Collected</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-800 text-slate-300 font-light">
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 font-medium text-slate-200">Apple App Store</td>
            <td class="p-4">In-App Purchases & Distribution</td>
            <td class="p-4">Transaction data, device identifiers, basic account metrics.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 font-medium text-slate-200">Google Play Store / Google Analytics</td>
            <td class="p-4">In-App Purchases & Telemetry</td>
            <td class="p-4">Transaction data, crash logs, device model, and aggregate usage statistics (e.g., session duration).</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 font-medium text-slate-200">GitHub Pages</td>
            <td class="p-4">Website Hosting</td>
            <td class="p-4">Standard server logs (including visitor IP addresses) collected automatically for security and network performance.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <hr class="border-slate-800 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-50 mb-4">4. Website Cookies and Analytics</h2>
    <p class="text-[15px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-10">
      Our website may use basic cookies or analytics in the future to optimize performance and analyze traffic. If implemented, these tools will respect your browser's "Do Not Track" signals, and you will be prompted with a cookie consent banner where required by law.
    </p>

    <hr class="border-slate-800 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-50 mb-4">5. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p class="text-[15px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-10">
      The App is restricted to individuals <strong class="text-slate-100 font-medium">aged 13 and older</strong>. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we discover that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information (via support emails, for instance), we will delete it immediately.
    </p>

    <hr class="border-slate-800 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-50 mb-4">6. Your Legal Rights (FADP & GDPR)</h2>
    <p class="text-[15px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Depending on your residency (such as Switzerland or the European Economic Area), you possess the following rights regarding data processing:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-[15px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-10 pl-2">
      <li><strong class="text-slate-100 font-medium">Right to Access:</strong> You can export all your App data anytime via the local .csv download feature.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-slate-100 font-medium">Right to Erasure:</strong> You can delete all your App data instantly via the settings inside the App.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-slate-100 font-medium">Right to Information:</strong> You can contact us at info@returnapp.org to ask what data (if any, such as support emails) we have concerning you.</li>
    </ul>

    <hr class="border-slate-800 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-50 mb-4">7. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p class="text-[15px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-10">
      We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page with an updated "Last Updated" date. You are advised to review this page periodically for any modifications.
    </p>

    <hr class="border-slate-800 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-50 mb-4">8. Contact Information</h2>
    <p class="text-[15px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed">
      For any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, your rights, or our data handling practices, please reach out to us at: 
      <a href="mailto:info@returnapp.org" class="text-sapphire-400 hover:text-sapphire-300 transition-colors">info@returnapp.org</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>